b-pawn. It depends on the concrete position and it should be calculated. In
this position, dxc4 is better since bxc4 would allow e4!} dxc4 $1 (17... bxc4
18. e4 $1 (18. Rfd1 $2 Rfe8 19. Rb2 Ne4 20. Nxe4 Rxe4 $19 {[%csl Rb4,Gc4]
Black's protected passed c4-pawn is a great asset, and White's b4-pawn is very
weak.}) 18... dxe4 19. Nxe4 Nxe4 20. Qxe4 Rfe8 21. Qc2 Qxd4 22. Rfd1 Qf4 $11)
18. Rfd1 Nd5 $1 19. e4 (19. Ne4 Qg6 20. Rdc1 f5 21. Nc5 Ra7 $17) 19... Nxc3 20.
Qxc3 Rfe8 21. f3 Rad8 $17) 16. a5 $16 Re7 17. Rfc1 Rae8 18. Ne2 Nf8 19. Ng3 g6
