{[%evp 0,24,19,19,13,2,2,2,24,18,13,8,44,44,44,23,23,24,28,17,39,28,32,20,20,
21,21]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 h6 4. cxd5 $5 exd5 5. Bf4 {White's idea with
this move order is to develop the g1-knight to e2 with e3, Bd3, and Nge2.
Black has several good ways to choose from against this system.} c6 $5 {
Black wants to develop the light-squared bishop and after this move, Qb3 can
be met with ... Qb6.} (5... Nf6 $5 {This is also playable.} 6. e3 Bd6 7. Bxd6
Qxd6 8. Bd3 O-O 9. Nge2 b6 $1 10. O-O (10. Nf4 Rd8 11. O-O Bb7 12. Rc1 c5 $132)
10... Rd8 11. Rc1 c5 $132) 6. e3 (6. Nf3 Bf5 $1 {Black shouldn't miss the
opportunity to develop this bishop.} 7. e3 Nf6 (7... Bd6 8. Bxd6 Qxd6 9. Bd3
Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nf6 $11) 8. Bd3 Bxd3 9. Qxd3 Be7 $5 10. O-O O-O 11. h3 Nbd7 $11)
(6. Qc2 Ne7 $1 {[%csl Gf5][%cal Gc8f5] Now Bf5 will come with tempo.} 7. e3 Bf5
8. Bd3 (8. Qb3 Qb6 $11) 8... Bxd3 9. Qxd3 Ng6 10. Bg3 Bd6 $132 (10... Nd7 $132)
) 6... Bf5 $5 (6... Ne7 $5 {This is another good way to continue. 6...Ne7 is a
useful waiting move.} 7. Bd3 (7. Nf3 Bf5 8. Be2 Ng6 9. Bg3 Nd7 10. O-O Be7 {
With a similar position.}) 7... Bf5 8. Nf3 Bxd3 9. Qxd3 Ng6 10. Bg3 Nd7 11. O-O
Be7 12. Rac1 O-O 13. h3 Nb6 14. b3 Bd6 15. Bxd6 Qxd6 $132) 7. Bd3 (7. g4 $1 {
The best move according to the computer. After 7.g4, Black goes back to h7 or
e6, but in any case, Black has a very healthy position while White exposed
their kingside a bit.} Bh7 $132 (7... Be6 8. h3 (8. Qb3 Qb6 {The typical
response after any Qb3.}) 8... h5 $132) 8. h4 (8. Qb3 Qb6) 8... Bd6 9. Nh3 Ne7
$132) (7. Nf3 $6 Nd7 8. Be2 Ngf6 9. O-O Be7 10. Ne5 O-O 11. Rc1 Nxe5 12. Bxe5
Bd6 13. Bxd6 (13. Bxf6 Qxf6 14. Bd3 Bd7 $1 $17 {Black is keeping another pair
of minor pieces which will help in the attack on White's king later.}) 13...
Qxd6 14. Bd3 Ng4 (14... Bxd3 15. Qxd3 Rae8 16. a3 Re7 17. b4 a6 18. Rb1 Ng4 19.
g3 h5 20. Rfe1 (20. a4 Qh6 21. b5 h4 $19) 20... Qf6 21. Qd2 h4 $19) 15. g3 Bxd3
16. Qxd3 Rae8 17. a3 h5 $15) 7... Bxd3 8. Qxd3 Bd6 $1 (8... Nf6 {Is also
possible.} 9. Nf3 Nbd7 10. O-O Be7 11. Ne5 O-O 12. Rac1 Re8 13. h3 Nxe5 14.
Bxe5 Nd7 15. Bg3 Nb6 16. b3 Nc8 {Black wants to play Bd6 and then to be able
to recapture with the knight on d6.} 17. Rfd1 Bd6 18. Bxd6 Nxd6 $15) 9. Nge2
Ne7 10. O-O O-O 11. f3 Na6 $1 12. a3 Nc7 $11 0-1

