1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 h6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bf4 Bd6 {This is the starting
position of the Queen's Gambit where White doesn't include the exchange
cxd5-exd5. White has a choice of several different moves like Bxd6, Bg3, Ne5,
and e3.} 6. Bxd6 {In my opinion, this is the most accurate move for White.} (6.
e3 {After this move, Black's plan is: Bxf4, dxc4, 0-0, Nc6, Ne7, and b6 with
Bb7. The analysis can be found in the theoretical chapter.}) 6... Qxd6 {
Black's plan is to play 0-0 and then Qe7! if needed, in order to make a useful
move while waiting for White to spend a tempo developing the light-squared
bishop, and then capture dxc4 and push c5!} 7. e3 O-O 8. Bd3 dxc4 9. Bxc4 c5 {
With a playable position for Black.} *

