1. d4 (1. c4 e6 2. Nc3 (2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 Nf6 {This is going to take the game
into Catalan territory.}) 2... d5 3. d4 h6 {Reaches the starting position in
the repertoire.}) (1. Nf3 d5 {This is an acceptable move order for entering
the repertoire.} (1... Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 d5 4. d4 h6 {Is also an acceptable
move order.}) 2. c4 e6 {It will transpose either to the Queen's Gambit with 3..
.h6 or the Catalan.}) 1... d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 (3. Nf3 h6 {For those who want
to aim for the maximum, 3...Nf6 is best, and for those who want to study less,
3...h6 can be also played here. My recommendation is to simply play 3...h6
with the idea after 4.Nc3, 4.g3, and 4.Bf4, to transpose to the analyzed
repertoire, however, if White is a Colle system player, 4.e3 can be played
where the move h6 is slightly inaccurate, although the position is around
equal and definitely playable.} (3... Nf6 4. Bg5 {Trying to transpose in the
