very interesting when White plays Rh4. Black gets an isolated pawn but opens
up the position, and in addition, the rook on h4 can turn out to be misplaced.}
10. g4 (10. cxd5 exd5 11. dxc5 Nxc5 12. Rd4 Be6 $132 {White's king is still in
the center and would require several moves to get to safety.} 13. Bc4 Qa5 {
Black has a good play with the better-placed pieces.} (13... dxc4 $6 {Almost
works, but there is no need for it anyway.} 14. Rxd8 Rfxd8 15. Nd4 $16)) 10...
Ne4 $1 11. cxd5 Nxc3 12. bxc3 exd5 13. dxc5 Nxc5 $15) 10. g4 (10. cxd5 exd5 11.
Rc1 (11. Bd3 Re8 12. Qc2 c5 13. dxc5 bxc5 14. O-O-O Nb6 $17) (11. g4 Ne4 {
The usual move after White plays g4.}) 11... Bb7 12. Bd3 (12. g4 Ne4 $15) 12...
c5 (12... Re8 $2 13. Nb5 $16) 13. dxc5 (13. g4 $6 Ne4 14. Kf1 Rc8 15. Rh3 a6
$15 (15... Re8 $15)) 13... bxc5 14. Kf1 Re8 15. Kg1 Qe7 $36) (10. Bd3 Bb7 11.
Kf1 c5 (11... dxc4 12. Bxc4 c5 $36) 12. cxd5 Nxd5 $13 (12... exd5 13. dxc5 bxc5
{Black has a very nice play with the pawns on c5 and d5, and Black is fighting
to take over the advantage.})) (10. Qc2 Bb7 11. cxd5 exd5 $132 (11... Nxd5 $132
)) 10... Ne4 $1 {White can't capture the knight on e4 since the rook on h4
will be hanging at the end.} 11. cxd5 (11. Rc1 Bb7 $15 (11... Nxc3 {Is also
possible.} 12. Rxc3 Bb7 $15)) 11... exd5 $1 12. Nxd5 Bb7 13. Bc4 (13. Nc3 $2
Nxc3 14. bxc3 Bxf3 15. Qxf3 Qxh4) (13. Nf4 $2 g5 $19 (13... Nxf2 $19 {[%csl
Rh4][%cal Gb7f3]} 14. Kxf2 Bxf3 15. gxf3 Qxh4+ $19)) 13... b5 14. Bb3 c5 $36 {
Black has the initiative and full compensation for the pawn.} *

