1. d4 (1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. Nf3 {Black shouldn't play ...h6 since
White is not threatening Bg5.} Bd6 {Black also has other good moves in the
position, however, this move is consistent with the repertoire.} 5. O-O O-O {
Black is following the same moves. Black's next moves can be dxc4, Nc6, and
e5! - the usual plan.} 6. d4 h6 7. Nc3 Nc6 {Transposing to the main line of
the Catalan with Nc3.}) 1... Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 h6 5. Bg2 Bd6 6. O-O
O-O 7. Nc3 Nc6 8. Nb5 dxc4 {The correct move after 8.Nb5.} 9. Qc2 e5 (9... a6
$1 $15 {This is a better move than 9...e5.} 10. Nxd6 cxd6 11. Qxc4 Ne7 $1 {
[%cal Gb7b5,Gc8b7]} 12. Qd3 (12. Bf4 Ned5 $15) (12. Bd2 b5 13. Qd3 Bb7 14. Ne1
(14. Rac1 Be4 $15) 14... Bxg2 15. Nxg2 Qb6 16. e4 Rfc8 $15) 12... Bd7 {12...b5
wasn't with tempo anymore, so 12...Bd7 is better in this case.} 13. Re1 Bb5 $15
14. Qd1 Bc6 {With a slightly better position for Black.}) 10. Nxd6 cxd6 11.
dxe5 dxe5 12. Qxc4 Be6 13. Qb5 e4 14. Ne5 Nd4 15. Qxb7 Qd6 16. Bf4 Nxe2+ 17.
Kh1 Nxf4 18. gxf4 Rfb8 19. Qc6 Qxc6 20. Nxc6 Rxb2 21. a3 Bc4 22. Rfe1 Rxf2 23.
Bxe4 Nxe4 24. Rxe4 Be6 25. Kg1 Rc2 26. Nb4 Rd2 27. Rc1 Kh7 28. Na6 Rad8 29. h4
Ra2 30. Re3 Rdd2 31. Rg3 h5 32. Nb4 Rab2 33. Nc6 a6 34. Ne5 Bd5 35. Rg5 g6 36.
Nd7 Kg7 37. Ne5 Ra2 38. Rg3 Rg2+ 39. Rxg2 Rxg2+ 40. Kf1 Ra2 41. Rc3 Rh2 42. Rc5
Be6 43. Nf3 Ra2 44. Rc3 a5 45. Ng5 Kf6 46. Ke1 a4 47. Nf3 Kf5 48. Nd4+ Kg4 49.
Nxe6 fxe6 50. Re3 Kf5 51. Re5+ Kxf4 52. Rxe6 Kf5 53. Re3 Rh2 54. Rf3+ Ke5 55.
Rg3 Kf5 56. Rf3+ Ke6 57. Rf4 Ke5 58. Rxa4 Kf5 59. Rb4 Ke5 60. Kf1 Kd5 61. Kg1
Rh3 62. a4 Kc5 63. Rf4 Kd5 64. Kg2 Ra3 65. Rb4 Kc5 66. Rf4 Kd5 67. Rb4 Kc5 68.
Rf4 Kd5 1/2-1/2

