1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 h6 5. Bg2 Bd6 6. O-O O-O 7. Nc3 Nc6 8. Qc2
$6 dxc4 {Black wants to play ...e5 next.} 9. Rd1 {Preventing ...e5 and
threatening e2-e4, since Black can't meet e4 with the typical e6-e5!} Qe7 {
Making e5 possible again, and Black is doing well.} 10. Nb5 (10. e4 e5 $15 11.
d5 $6 Nb4 12. Qe2 Nd3 $17) 10... Bd7 {This is a normal move, but 10...a6 is
better.} (10... a6 $1 11. Nxd6 cxd6 12. Qxc4 {Black can't play Ne7 in this
version, but developing with Bd7 is good enough.} Bd7 13. Bd2 Na7 $1 $15 {
The light-squared bishop from d7 can now be activated on c6 or b5, depending
on what White plays.} 14. Qb3 Bc6 15. Rac1 Bd5 16. Qd3 Rfc8 $15) 11. Qxc4 a6
12. Nxd6 cxd6 13. Bd2 Rfc8 14. Qb3 b5 15. Rdc1 Be8 16. e3 Rc7 17. Ne1 Rac8 18.
Nd3 Nd7 19. d5 exd5 20. Qxd5 Nce5 21. Rxc7 Rxc7 22. Bb4 Nxd3 23. Bxd6 Qf6 24.
Qxd3 Qxb2 25. Qb1 1/2-1/2

