dxc4 9. bxc4 e5 10. d5 $6 {This is never good for White.} Na5 {Black always
plays Na5 and b6.} 11. Nd2 b6 {Black's light-squared bishop can be developed
to a6.} 12. Qc2 (12. e4 Ba6 13. Qe2 Rc8 {Intending ...c6.} 14. Bb2 c6 {Opening
up the c-file and targeting White's c4-pawn.}) 12... Bd7 13. Qd3 (13. Nce4 Nxe4
