1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 h6 5. Bg2 Bd6 6. Qc2 O-O 7. O-O b6 8. cxd5
exd5 9. Nc3 Re8 {Black is setting up a small positional trap.} 10. Nb5 Bd7 11.
Nxd6 cxd6 {This was Black's idea with 9...Re8. The bishop is better placed on
d7 instead of b7.} 12. Bf4 Qe7 13. Rfe1 (13. Qc7 Nc6 $15) 13... Nc6 14. Rac1 a5
15. Qb1 a4 (15... b5 $15 {With a slightly better position for Black. The rest
is an example of what should Black do if the queenside gets blockaded.} 16. a3
Rab8 17. b4 a4 {[%csl Gc4][%cal Gc6a7,Ga7c8,Gc8b6,Gb6c4] If the position gets
blocked on the queenside like this, Black's plan is to reroute the c6-knight
to c4.}) (15... Rac8 {Is also possible.} 16. Bd2 b5 17. a3 Ne4 $15) 16. b3 b5
17. h4 b4 $1 18. bxa4 Rxa4 $19 {Black can double the rooks on the a-file, Ne4
is an idea, and even Bf5 can be played after that.} 0-1

