{In this game, Black had a very good position, but then he gave White time to
reroute the f3-knight to c3, and reach a favorable version in that pawn
structure for White.} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 h6 5. Bg2 Bd6 6. O-O
O-O 7. Qc2 b6 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Nc3 Bb7 10. Nb5 Nc6 11. Nxd6 cxd6 12. Bf4 Qd7 13.
Rac1 Rfe8 (13... a5 {Black can choose from many moves, and 13...a5 is one of
them.}) 14. Rfe1 Rac8 15. Qa4 Re4 (15... a6 {This is also a good move.}) 16.
Nd2 Re7 (16... Rxd4 {Black should have captured the pawn according to the
computer.}) 17. Nb1 a6 18. Nc3 $14 {A very good plan by Wojtaszek! Black lost
some time and allowed the knight from f3 to be rerouted to c3 from where it's
much better placed and it doesn't block the bishop from g2.} b5 19. Qd1 Na5 20.
b3 b4 21. Na4 Rxc1 22. Bxc1 Bc6 23. Nb2 Bb5 24. Nd3 Nc6 25. Nf4 Qf5 26. h3 Qb1
27. Qd2 Ne4 28. Qb2 Qxb2 29. Bxb2 Nc3 30. Bxc3 bxc3 31. a4 Nxd4 32. axb5 axb5
33. Kf1 Nxb3 34. Nxd5 Nd2+ 35. Kg1 Ra7 36. Nxc3 b4 37. Ne4 Nc4 38. Rb1 Ra4 39.
e3 f5 40. Nf6+ 1-0

