1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 (2. g3 {Here are some move orders with which the game can
transpose into the Queen's Gambit.} Nf6 3. Bg2 e6 {3...Bg4 or 3...c6 are the
best moves here for Black, in order to play a reversed Torre with a good
position, but 3...e6 aims to transpose to the analyzed repertoire.} 4. c4 (4.
O-O Bd6 5. d4 (5. d3 O-O 6. Nbd2 e5 {Black has control of the center and a
comfortable position.}) 5... h6) 4... Bd6) 2... e6 3. g3 Nf6 4. Bg2 Bd6 $5 {
Black has also other good moves to choose from, but with this move, Black
stays in the proposed repertoire. The move 4...Bd6 is a rare but completely
playable move and a great practical weapon for Black!} 5. O-O (5. d4 h6 {
When White creates the possibility for Bg5, Black prevents it with the move h6.
}) 5... O-O {White is still not threatening Bg5, so there is no need for ...h6.
If White tries something else other than transposing to the main lines, like
Qc2, Qb3, or Nc3, Black can simply capture the pawn on c4.} 6. b3 (6. Nc3 $6 {
With the knight on c3, Black can capture the pawn on c4 and it won't be easy
for White to regain it.} dxc4 $15 {In general, this move tends to be effective
when White's d-pawn is still on its starting square.} (6... Nc6 {Is also
playable and it's likely to transpose to what has already been analyzed,
however, 6...dxc4 is a much better move.} 7. d4 h6) 7. Qa4 a6 $1 {This move is
suggested by the computer.} (7... e5 $5 8. Qxc4 Nc6 9. d3 h6 $11 {Black has a
very nice version of the Reti and the knight on c6 is well-developed and
controls the center.}) 8. Qxc4 b5 9. Qb3 c5 10. d3 Bb7 11. a4 b4 12. Nb1 Nc6 $1
$13 (12... Nbd7 $6 13. Nbd2 $14)) (6. d4 h6 {Transposes to the Catalan.}) (6.
Qc2 dxc4 7. Qxc4 e5 8. d4 Nc6 $11 {Black can play this plan of dxc4, e5, and
Nc6, against many moves from White.}) 6... dxc4 $1 {This is the best move for
Black.} (6... b6 {Black doesn't have to know exact theory and can play logical
moves, and it's likely that the position will be similar or transpose to a
variation already analyzed, for example:} 7. Bb2 Bb7 8. d4 Nbd7 $11) 7. bxc4 e5
$1 8. Nc3 Re8 9. d3 h6 $5 (9... Na6 $1 {The knight is heading to the good
c5-square.} 10. Nd2 (10. Bg5 h6 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. Ne4 Qd8 13. Nxd6 Qxd6 14. Nd2
c6 $11) 10... c6 11. Bb2 Nc5 $13) 10. Rb1 c6 11. Qc2 Qc7 (11... Na6 $1 {
Is possible again.} 12. Nd2 Nc5 13. Bb2 Bf5 $36) 12. Nd2 Na6 13. Na4 Nc5 14.
Ba3 Nfd7 15. Rb2 b6 16. Nxc5 Bxc5 17. Bxc5 Nxc5 18. Nb3 Ne6 19. a4 Rb8 20. Rfb1
c5 21. Nc1 Bb7 22. Bxb7 Qxb7 23. a5 Qc6 24. Na2 Nd4 25. Qd1 e4 26. dxe4 Qxe4
27. Nc3 Qe6 28. Qd3 Rbd8 29. axb6 axb6 30. Rxb6 Qh3 31. Nd5 Nxe2+ 32. Kh1 Nd4
1/2-1/2

