1. c4 e6 2. Nc3 d5 3. d4 h6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e3 {Here are several strange and
kind of semi-waiting moves from White. Black shouldn't be worried about them
since they are not threatening and should simply play chess. I will show you
one of the many possible ways that Black can play against them which is good
and ambitious. The advantage of this system is that Black can play it against
any of these strange moves from White.} (5. a3) (5. h3) (5. Qc2 {This is the
most interesting out of the several semi-waiting moves since White may want to
play e4. Black can also play 5...a6 here, but there is a better option.} c5 {
Black is likely to get an isolated pawn.} 6. cxd5 exd5 7. dxc5 Bxc5 {Usually,
White shouldn't put the queen on c2 in positions that are playing against the
isolated pawn, so the queen is misplaced.}) (5. a3) 5... Nbd7 (5... a6 $1 {
Generally, after all of White's passive moves, I suggest the move a6! Black
intends to capture the pawn on c4 and play b5 with Bb7, with a very good
counterplay!} 6. Bd3 (6. c5 b6 $11) (6. cxd5 exd5 {It doesn't really matter
that Black spent a tempo on the move a6. Black's dark-squared bishop will go
to d6 and Black will have a good position.}) (6. b3 dxc4 (6... c5 $1 $36) 7.
bxc4 c5 $132) 6... dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 8. Bd3 c5 9. O-O (9. dxc5 Bxc5 10. O-O Bb7
$15) 9... Bb7 {It's important to understand the ideas in these types of
positions. Black will play Nbd7 next and Black doesn't want to capture on d4
since that would open up White's dark-squared bishop. White wants to develop
the bishop from c1 but is also running out of useful moves. Black will capture
on d4 only if White plays the move e4 first.} 10. e4 (10. a4 b4 $15) 10... cxd4
11. Nxd4 Nbd7 $15 {Capturing the knight wasn't possible due to Bxb5+. Black
has good control over the dark squares in this position.}) 6. Bd3 b6 7. cxd5
exd5 8. Bb5 Bb7 9. Ne5 Bd6 10. Qa4 c5 11. Bc6 Qc8 12. Bxb7 Qxb7 13. O-O a6 14.
Nxd7 Qxd7 15. dxc5 bxc5 16. Rd1 Ra7 17. b3 Be5 18. Bb2 O-O 19. Qxd7 Rxd7 20.
Rab1 Rfd8 21. Na4 Bxb2 22. Rxb2 c4 23. Kf1 cxb3 24. Rxb3 Rc7 25. Rc3 Rb7 26.
Rc2 Rb5 27. Ke2 g6 28. Rd4 Kg7 29. f3 Re8 30. Rb2 Rc8 31. Kd2 Ra5 32. Nc3 Rac5
33. Rd3 h5 34. Ne2 Ra5 35. Nd4 Ra4 36. Rc3 Rcc4 37. Rbc2 Nd7 38. Rxc4 dxc4 39.
Ne2 Nc5 40. Kc3 Nd3 41. Nd4 Nb4 42. Rd2 Nd5+ 43. Kc2 Rxa2+ 44. Kc1 Ra1+ 45. Kc2
Nxe3+ 46. Kb2 Rg1 47. g3 Rf1 48. Re2 Nd5 49. Rc2 c3+ 50. Kb3 Rb1+ 51. Ka3 Kf6
52. Ne2 Rh1 53. h4 Rf1 54. f4 Rf3 55. Kb3 a5 56. Ka4 Re3 57. Kxa5 Kf5 58. Kb5
Kg4 59. Kc4 Nf6 60. Rxc3 Rxe2 61. Kd4 0-1

